


=Quotes=
"In 247, a few years after Zhi Qian had left Jianye, the famous Sogdian monk Kang
Senghui arrived at the capital. He came from Jiaozhi, the provincial
capital of Jiaozhou in the extreme South of the empire (near present-day Hanoi). His
family had been living in India for generations; his father, a merchant, had come to
settle at this important commercial town." (Zürcher.1959: 51)

"Kang Senghui’s Buddhism formed a continuation of the Northern school of An
Shigao, An Xuan and Yan Fotiao with its stress upon dhyana." (Zürcher.1959: 53)